Package net.jhoogland.jautomata.semirings

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Semifield<K>
    Semifields must implement this interface.
    Semiring<K>
    Semirings must implement this interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BooleanSemiring
    Implementation of the Boolean semiring, which is a semiring of the Boolean values true and false.
    KTropicalSemiring<K extends Comparable<K>>
    This semiring is used by the shortest distance algorithm to determine the n shortest distances to a state.
    LogSemiring
    Implementation of the log semiring, which is a semiring of the set of non-negative real numbers (represented by double values in this implementation).
    PathWeight<K extends Comparable<K>>
    A chain of instances of this class specify a path over an automaton and its weight.
    RealSemiring
    Implementation of the semiring of non-negative real numbers (represented by double values in this implementation).
    TropicalSemiring
    Implementation of the tropical semiring, which is a semiring of the set of non-negative real numbers (represented by double values in this implementation).
